%META:TOPICPARENT{name="WebHome"}%
---+ Glossary

%TOC%

$ *ATLAS*: A Toroidal LHC ApparatuS. One of the two general-purpose experiments at the CERN LHC.

$ *ATHENA*: ATLAS' offline software framework (Gaudi-based). Produces the JiveXML that CGV Web reads.

$ *ATLANTIS*: The legacy Java event display. Still the source of the live event feed consumed by CGV Web (=atlas-live.cern.ch=).

$ *ATLAS-ID (compact)*: A 32-bit integer packing =(subDet, side, sampling, η-bin, φ-bin)= for every calorimeter cell. Decoded by CGV Web's WASM parser.

$ *Cell*: A single readout channel of a calorimeter sampling.

$ *Cluster*: A topological grouping of adjacent cells produced by ATHENA's =CaloTopoCluster=. Drawn as dashed red outlines.

$ *EB / LB*: Extended / Long barrel — the two tile-calorimeter cylinders.

$ *EMB / EMEC*: EM Barrel / EM End-Cap — the LAr electromagnetic calorimeters.

$ *FCAL*: Forward Calorimeter — three LAr modules at very high pseudorapidity (η 3.1–4.9).

$ *GeoModel*: ATLAS' unified detector-geometry description. The source-of-truth for CGV Web's =CaloGeometry.glb.gz=.

$ *Ghost*: An inactive support or cryostat volume. Rendered semi-transparent for spatial context.

$ *GLB / glTF*: Binary / JSON forms of the Khronos 3D asset format. Used for the packaged geometry.

$ *HEC*: Hadronic End-Cap calorimeter (LAr-based, 4 wheels).

$ *JiveXML*: XML event format used by ATLANTIS and CGV Web. See [[EventData]].

$ *P97*: The 97th percentile of the current event's cell energies for a given sub-detector. Used as the auto ceiling of each threshold slider.

$ *Sampling*: A depth layer inside a calorimeter (=EMB1=, =EMB2=, =TileA=, etc.).

$ *Tile*: Scintillating-tile hadronic calorimeter forming the central barrel of ATLAS.

$ *Track*: Inner-detector reconstructed trajectory. Drawn as thin yellow lines.

$ *WebGL2*: OpenGL ES 3.0 bindings for browsers. Required by Three.js and by CGV Web.

$ *η (eta)*: Pseudorapidity, =η = −ln tan(θ/2)=.

$ *φ (phi)*: Azimuthal angle around the beam axis.

